com.github.andreptb.fitnesse.selenium

Class WebDriverHelper

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.github.andreptb.fitnesse.selenium.WebDriverHelper

  • public class WebDriverHelper
extends Object
    Utility class that wraps WebDriver instances. Each connect(String, String, String) call will associate a working instance of WebDriver and will be used until quit() is used or another connect(String, String, String)

      • connect

        public void connect(String browser,
                    String capabilities,
                    String preferences)
             throws ReflectiveOperationException,
                    IOException
        Creates a WebDriver instance with desired browser and capabilities. Capabilities should follow a key/value format
        Parameters:
        browser - to be initialized. Can be a remote driver URL
        capabilities - string. Should follow a key/value format
        preferences - string. Should follow a key/value format
        Throws:
        ReflectiveOperationException - if remote driver class cannot be instantiated
        IOException - if IO error occurs if invalid URL is used when connecting to remote drivers
        See Also:
        WebDriverCapabilitiesHelper.parse(String, String, String)

      • getWhenAvailable

        public String getWhenAvailable(String from,
                               BiFunction<org.openqa.selenium.WebDriver,SeleniumLocatorParser.WebElementSelector,String> callback)
        Core function designed to provide callbacks with selenium context necessary to evaluate commands. Applies the following rules:
        • Builds the context and passes the control to the callback (see SeleniumLocatorParser.parse(String))
        • If the callback is unable to find a WebElement to run commmands, or fails for any other reason, the callback will be reinvoked until a positive return happens or getTimeoutInSeconds() is reached
        • If the callback returns positively and the result don't match with SeleniumLocatorParser.WebElementSelector.getExpectedValue(), the callback will be reinvoked until the value matches or getTimeoutInSeconds() is reached
        • If the callback returns positively and the result match with SeleniumLocatorParser.WebElementSelector.getExpectedValue() (or SeleniumLocatorParser.WebElementSelector.getExpectedValue() is empty), the result will be returned
        Parameters:
        from - selenium selector received by the fixture@param from
        callback - The callback to be invoked with SeleniumLocatorParser.WebElementSelector and WebDriver
        Returns:
        the value returned from the callback
        Throws:
        WebDriverHelper.StopTestWithWebDriverException - if isBrowserAvailable() returns false or if getStopTestOnFirstFailure() is true and any failure occurs
